│ poison where the\n        // original did not. Disable vectorization of     │
│ such compares by treating\n        // them as reduced values.\n        //   │
│ However, we must also consider that the compare may be used as a\n          │
│ // condition in a select that is a boolean logic op (select with            │
│ true/false).\n        // In that case, the compare is already a boolean     │
│ value and should be\n        // considered as a reduced value, not as a     │
│ reduction operation.\n        // The function isBoolLogicOp identifies such │
│ selects.\n        // If the compare is used by a select that is a boolean   │
